				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Part of my hypothesis for this, if you'll recall, is the asset complexity gap between NES and Super NES. It appears to be confirmed by <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=217194#p217194" class="postlink">this review of <em>Sydney Hunter</em></a>, which took marks off for underusing the S-PPU. Apparently you <em>have</em> to have parallax, not just TG16-class graphics, if you want to sell a Super NES game.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

